rComments: He was the best out of the three profs. Too bad he was the last prof and my foundation for reactions was screwed up by then.

My fav of the 3 lecturers. the material is extremely difficult but his slides are amazingly organized and helpful! explains concepts very throughly but concisely -doesn't ramble on. pretty chill dude who makes coming to 9am lecture not ridiculously boring and exhausting. allows plenty of time for in-class questions (super helpful!) :)

Good prof, clear and concise. Pretty chill guy, very approachable. Organic chem is not something that's easy to grasp for some people but he explains it well enough that you get the picture. Read the textbook to understand better and DO THE TUTORIAL QUESTIONS. Cannot stress this enough!
